    "answer_id" : 2850644,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<p>Well, this is a solution using no \"magic\" regexes, or other complex sdk features.</p>\n\n<p>Obviously, the regex matcher is probably better to use in real life, as its quicker to write. (And it is probably bug free too...)</p>\n\n<p>On the other hand, You should be able to understand whats going on here...</p>\n\n<p>If you want to handle the case \\r\\n as a single new-line (msdos-convention) you have to add your own code.  Hint, you need another variable that keeps track of the previous character matched...</p>\n\n<pre><code>int lines= 1;\n\nfor( int pos = 0; pos &lt; yourInput.length(); pos++){\n    char c = yourInput.charAt(pos);\n    if( c == \"\\r\" || c== \"\\n\" ) {\n        lines++;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7896,
      "reputation" : 6731,
      "user_id" : 13905,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/g8FXH.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "volley",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/13905/volley"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1274122184,
    "creation_date" : 1274122184,
    "answer_id" : 2851828,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
    "body" : "<pre><code>new StringTokenizer(str, \"\\r\\n\").countTokens();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note that this will not count empty lines (\\n\\n).</p>\n\n<p>CRLF (\\r\\n) counts as single line break.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 228679,
      "reputation" : 332,
      "user_id" : 491144,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0b1f396a67963bec5b2e6021509c1080?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Saxintosh",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/491144/saxintosh"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1328536013,
    "creation_date" : 1328536013,
    "answer_id" : 9161032,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This is a quicker version:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int countLines(String str)\n{\n    if (str == null || str.length() == 0)\n        return 0;\n    int lines = 1;\n    int len = str.length();\n    for( int pos = 0; pos &lt; len; pos++) {\n        char c = str.charAt(pos);\n        if( c == '\\r' ) {\n            lines++;\n            if ( pos+1 &lt; len &amp;&amp; str.charAt(pos+1) == '\\n' )\n                pos++;\n        } else if( c == '\\n' ) {\n            lines++;\n        }\n    }\n    return lines;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 7342678,
