      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/246263/veger"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 22,
    "last_activity_date" : 1430772923,
    "last_edit_date" : 1430772923,
    "creation_date" : 1379272030,
    "answer_id" : 18816371,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>A very simple solution, which does not create String objects, arrays or other (complex) objects, is to use the following:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public static int countLines(String str) {\n    if(str == null || str.isEmpty())\n    {\n        return 0;\n    }\n    int lines = 1;\n    int pos = 0;\n    while ((pos = str.indexOf(\"\\n\", pos) + 1) != 0) {\n        lines++;\n    }\n    return lines;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Note, that if you use other EOL terminators you need to modify this example a little.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 201157,
      "reputation" : 13125,
      "user_id" : 447426,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 62,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/Atn2u.jpg?s=256",
