    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1482009590,
    "creation_date" : 1482009590,
    "answer_id" : 41203172,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This method will allocate an array of chars, it should be used instead of iterating over string.length() as length() uses number of Unicode characters rather than chars.</p>\n\n<pre><code>int countChars(String str, char chr) {\n    char[] charArray = str.toCharArray();\n    int count = 0;\n    for(char cur : charArray)\n        if(cur==chr) count++;\n    return count;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 8769118,
      "reputation" : 58,
      "user_id" : 6556545,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/oVm9u.png?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Javanaut",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/6556545/javanaut"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1496419650,
    "creation_date" : 1496419650,
    "answer_id" : 44333204,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Try this one:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public int countLineEndings(String str){\n\n    str = str.replace(\"\\r\\n\", \"\\n\"); // convert windows line endings to linux format \n    str = str.replace(\"\\r\", \"\\n\"); // convert (remaining) mac line endings to linux format\n\n    return str.length() - str.replace(\"\\n\", \"\").length(); // count total line endings\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>number of lines = countLineEndings(str) + 1</p>\n\n<p>Greetings :) </p>\n"
  }, {
