    "last_activity_date" : 1612403578,
    "last_edit_date" : 1612403578,
    "creation_date" : 1527794584,
    "answer_id" : 50631407,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>With Java-11 and above you can do the same using the <strong><a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/11/docs/api/java.base/java/lang/String.html#lines()\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>String.lines()</code></a></strong> API as follows :</p>\n<pre><code>String sample = &quot;Hello\\nWorld\\nThis\\nIs\\t&quot;;\nSystem.out.println(sample.lines().count()); // returns 4\n</code></pre>\n<p>The API doc states the following as a portion of it for the description:-</p>\n<blockquote>\n<pre><code>Returns:\nthe stream of lines extracted from this string\n</code></pre>\n</blockquote>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 904735,
      "reputation" : 413,
      "user_id" : 939857,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 0,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a7930a34f9331ede7d7de1444eded22c?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "user939857",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/939857/user939857"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1533479261,
    "creation_date" : 1533479261,
    "answer_id" : 51695203,
    "question_id" : 2850203,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>//import java.util.regex.Matcher;\n//import java.util.regex.Pattern;\n\nprivate static Pattern newlinePattern = Pattern.compile(\"\\r\\n|\\r|\\n\");\n\npublic static int lineCount(String input) {\n    Matcher m = newlinePattern.matcher(input);\n    int count = 0;\n    int matcherEnd = -1;\n    while (m.find()) {\n        matcherEnd = m.end();\n        count++;\n    }\n    if (matcherEnd &lt; input.length()) {\n        count++;\n    }\n\n    return count;\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This will count the last line if it doesn't end in cr/lf cr lf</p>\n"
  }, {
